[src:acts-of-union-1800/10-geo-4-p01] This is a complete **list of acts of the Parliament of the United Kingdom for the year 1829**.
[src:acts-of-union-1800/10-geo-4-p01] Note that the first parliament of the United Kingdom was held in 1801; parliaments between 1707 and 1800 were either parliaments of Great Britain or of Ireland).
[src:acts-of-union-1800/10-geo-4-p01] For acts passed up until 1707, see the list of acts of the Parliament of England and the list of acts of the Parliament of Scotland.
[src:acts-of-union-1800/10-geo-4-p01] For acts passed from 1707 to 1800, see the list of acts of the Parliament of Great Britain.
[src:acts-of-union-1800/10-geo-4-p01] Acts passed before 1963 are cited using this number, preceded by the year(s) of the reign during which the relevant parliamentary session was held; thus the Union with Ireland Act 1800 is cited as "39 & 40 Geo.
[src:acts-of-union-1800/10-geo-4-p01] Acts passed from 1963 onwards are simply cited by calendar year and chapter number.
[src:acts-of-union-1800/10-geo-4-p01] All modern acts have a short title, e.g. the Local Government Act 2003.
[src:acts-of-union-1800/10-geo-4-p01] Some earlier acts also have a short title given to them by later acts, such as by the Short Titles Act 1896.
[src:acts-of-union-1800/10-geo-4-p01] The third session of the 8th Parliament of the United Kingdom, which met from 5 February 1829 until 24 June 1829.
